def: A highly elastic wood, used for fishing rods, etc. The tree isunknown, but it is thought to be East Indian.
Long duration of life; length of life.The instances of longevity are chiefly amongst the abstemious.Arbuthnot.
An opinion opposed to some accepted standard. [Obs.] Sir T.Browne.
Of or pertaining to characters developed by the use of heat;pertaining to the characters of minerals when examined before theblowpipe; as, the pyrognostic characters of galena.
The time of the new moon; the beginning of the month in thelunar calendar.

An open air concert in the morning, as distinguished from anevening serenade; also, a pianoforte composition suggestive ofmorning. Grove.The crowing cock . . . Sang his aubade with lusty voice and clear.Longfellow.
Costly; expensive. [Obs.]The fineness of the gold and chargeful fashion. Shak.
The quality or state of being mannerly; civility; complaisance.Sir M. Hale.

A carbonate in which but half the hydrogen of the acid isreplaced by a positive element or radical, thus making the proportionof the acid to the positive or basic portion twice what it is in thenormal carbonates; an acid carbonate; -- sometimes calledsupercarbonate.
One who fars. Sir P. Sidney.
